Put a large #saucepan{} of water on to boil for the noodles. Halve, peel and thinly slice the @red onion{1/2}. Halve the @bell pepper{1}, and discard the core and seeds. Slice into thin strips. Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1/2} (or use a garlic press).

Heat a splash of @oil{a splash} in a large #frying pan{} or #wok{} over high heat. When the oil is very hot, add half the @beef strips{240%g}. Stir-fry until nicely browned but not cooked through, ~{2-3%minutes}. Transfer to a #plate{} and then repeat with the remaining strips. Keep to one side we will add them back to the stir-fry later. Wipe the pan clean when it has cooled down.

When the water in the saucepan boiling, add the @egg noodle nests{2}. Stir and lower the heat to medium. Cook for ~{4%minutes} then drain into a #colander{}. Cool under cold running water to stop them sticking together.

Return the frying pan or wok to high heat and add a splash of @oil{a splash}. Add all the veggies (@mangetout{150%g} and @sweet & sour garnish{5}) and stir-fry until the mangetout are tender, ~{6-7%minutes}.

> Add a splash of water half way through to help the veggies cook.

Once the veggies are soft, lower the heat to medium and add the garlic. Cook for ~{1%minute} then return the steak strips and any juices to the pan. Stir in the @sweet & sour sauce{50%g} along with the @water{75%g}(for the sauce). Bring to a bubble and stir through the noodles. Stir and heat until everything is piping. Get ready to serve.

Share the sweet and sour beef between your bowls. Sprinkle on @?sesame seeds{7.5%g} for those that like them. Enjoy!